# tspy — TrikeShed Python

Native Python implementation of the PRELOAD.md kernel algebra (Join, Twin, Series, Cursor, α-projection, ↺ left-identity, etc.).

## Installation

```bash
pip install -e /path/to/TrikeShed/libs/tspy
```

## Quick Start

```python
from tspy import (
    Join, Twin, Series, twin,
    j, alpha, α, left_identity,
    _l, _a, _s, s_,
    series_of, series_range, series_repeat,
    cursor_from_columns,
)

# Join algebra
j = Join(1, "hello")
t = twin(42)  # Twin(42, 42)

# Series algebra
s = series_of(1, 2, 3, 4, 5)
assert s.size == 5
assert s[0] == 1
assert list(s.view) == [1, 2, 3, 4, 5]

# α (alpha) lazy projection
doubled = s @ (lambda x: x * 2)  # or alpha(s, lambda x: x * 2)
assert list(doubled.view) == [2, 4, 6, 8, 10]

# Unicode operators
doubled = α(s, lambda x: x * 2)

# ↺ (left_identity) constant anchor
thunk = left_identity(42)
assert thunk() == 42

# Composition literals
_l[1, 2, 3]  # [1, 2, 3]
_s[1, 2, 2, 3]  # {1, 2, 3}
s_[1, 2, 3]  # Series(3, ...)

# Cursor algebra
cursor = cursor_from_columns(
    ["name", "age"],
    series_of("Alice", "Bob", "Carol"),
    series_of(30, 25, 35)
)
assert cursor.size == 3
row0 = cursor[0]
assert row0[0].a == "Alice"
assert row0[0].b()["name"] == "name"
assert row0[1].a == 30

# Cursor operations
sliced = cursor_range(cursor, 1, 3)  # cursor[1:3]
joined = join_cursors(c1, c2)  # widen horizontally
combined = combine_cursors(c1, c2)  # concatenate vertically
```

## Algebra Reference

| Symbol | Name | Description |
|--------|------|-------------|
| `Join<A, B>` | Join | Base binary composition |
| `Twin<T>` | Twin | Same-typed Join |
| `Series<T>` | Series | `Join<int, (int) -> T>` |
| `j(a, b)` | j | Infix Join constructor |
| `s @ f` | α | Lazy projection (map) |
| `x.↺` | ↺ | Left identity: `lambda: x` |
| `_l[...]` | List | List literal |
| `_s[...]` | Set | Set literal |
| `s_[...]` | Series | Series literal |

